# Refund Payment Service

This prompt is a demo target for `pdd coverage --contracts`.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Reject zero amount
The system MUST reject refund requests whose amount is zero or negative.

R2 - Prevent over-refund
The system MUST NOT refund more than the original charge amount.

R3 - Skip provider for invalid refunds
The system MUST NOT call the payment provider when local validation fails.

R4 - Preserve retry idempotency
The system MUST reuse the original idempotency key when retrying a refund.

R5 - Audit successful refunds
The system MUST write an audit log entry after a successful refund.

R6 - Provider secret isolation
The system MUST NOT log payment provider credentials.

R7 - Receipt delivery
The system MUST emit a receipt event after a confirmed refund.
</contract_rules>

<vocabulary>
refund amount: the monetary amount requested for return to the customer
original charge amount: the captured payment amount before refunds
idempotency key: stable request key used to deduplicate retry attempts
payment provider: the external API that processes payment refunds
receipt event: a durable event consumed by customer notification workers
</vocabulary>

<coverage>
R1: story__refund_invalid.md, test_R1_rejects_zero_refund
R2: story__refund_invalid.md
R3: test_R3_no_provider_call_invalid
R4: story__refund_idempotency.md
R5: TODO add audit-log story and test
R6: WAIVED W1
R7: story__refund_receipt_failed.md
</coverage>

<waivers>
W1:
  Rule: R6
  Approved by: security-review
  Rationale: Provider SDK handles credentials; this module never receives raw secrets.
  Expires: 2026-12-01
</waivers>

<deliverables>
Generate implementation code only.
</deliverables>

